50|$|The <b>Monochrome</b> <b>Display</b> Adapter (MDA, also MDA card, <b>Monochrome</b> <b>Display</b> and Printer Adapter, MDPA) is IBM's {{standard}} {{video display}} card and computer display {{standard for the}} PC introduced in 1981. The MDA {{does not have any}} pixel-addressable graphics modes. It has only a single monochrome text mode (PC video mode 7), which can display 80 columns by 25 lines of high resolution text characters or symbols useful for drawing forms.|$|R
